1) Full Load 
involve complete dataset

Pattern: Full Load
Problem: data changes few times a week, small dataset, lack of last updated value, homogeneous dataset
Solution: Extract and Load 
Consequences: 

a) Data volume: dynamic data voolume is a challenge
b) Data consistency: overwrites data and might loss some data

2) Incremental Load
Pattern: Incremental Loader
suitable for continuosly growing dataset

Problem: need to integrate only new data, data are immutable
Solution: 
a) Delta column: to indentify rows added since the last run, eg: ingestion time
b) time-partitioned datasets: tiome based to detect the whole nes chunk of data to be ingested.
Consequences: 
a) hard deletes:mutable data, if deletes, but can be overcomed using soft deletes or mark the new data as delete
b) backfilling: need to do a one shot full load and may involves more rows, can limit the ingestion chunk by chunking it based on time

Pattern: Change Data Capture
-for lower ingestion latency, built-in support for physical deletes
Problem: Incremental load is slow, if needed to be faster like every 30 seconds.
Solution: take data from a commit log, can modify data based on it.
Consequences: 

a) more complex as needs orchestration layer
b) only able to do this after starting the client process and previous data cannot be applied
c) the payload may have other info, need to filter it out.
c) data semantics, data might not be there yet if joins between 2 tables are required.

3) Replication
copy data from one location to another

Pattern: Passthrough Replicator
Problem: want to have the production dataset in dev and staging development.
Solution: Extract and Loadjob based on a replication policy.
Consequences: 
a)keep it simple
b) security issue in different environment
c) Personal Indentifiable Information  (use Transformation Replicator pattern)
d) Latency: infractructure based implementation will have latency, check with SLA on the permitted time frame
e) Metadata: skipping the metadata might make the dataset unusable

Pattern: Transformation Replicator

Problem: Data contains PII
Solution: 
a) Custom Mapping Function
b) SQL Select Statement
Consequences:
a) Transformation risk for text file formats.
b) Desynchronization

